 of Japanese mass culture actively search for intimacy and identity amid the powerful corporate structures that produce the leisure and entertainment of today's Japan.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aPopular culturezJapanxHistoryy20th century. 4aAnthropology and Archaeology : Anthropology. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aAsian Studies : Japanese Studies. 4aCultural Studies : Popular Culture. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh1 aBrau, Lorie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCondry, Ian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHosokawa, Shuhei, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKelly, William W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKelly, William W., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMatsuoka, Hideaki, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStevens, Carolyn S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThorn, Matthew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTierney, R. Kenji, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYano, Christine R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791485385423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791485385/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles